AN ACT to amend Tennessee Code Annotated, Title 68,
Chapter 221, Part 9, relative to the Water and
Wastewater Operator Certification Act.
BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE:
SECTION 1. Tennessee Code Annotated, Section 68-221-906(7), is amended by
deleting the subdivision and substituting instead:
(7) Prepare, conduct, and grade examinations in accordance with ยง 68-221-916;
SECTION 2. Tennessee Code Annotated, Title 68, Chapter 221, Part 9, is amended by
adding the following as a new section:
68-221-916.
(a) Examinations prepared and administered by the board must:
(1) Demonstrate that an operator has the necessary skills, knowledge,
ability, and judgment, as appropriate, for the specified operator classification of
the certification program pursuant to ยง 68-221-907;
(2) Consist of the same questions for all applicants; and
(3) Include a minimum of ten percent (10%) of the total questions for
each classification on state regulatory questions germane to the specific operator
classification.
(b) To receive a certificate, applicants must:
(1) Correctly answer seventy percent (70%) or more of:
(A) The total questions on an examination; and
(B) The state regulatory questions described in subdivision (a)(3);
